WEBVTT

00:01.630 --> 00:04.667
Previously on Elementary...
I understand _how
the cartel IS running now.

00:04.700 --> 00:06.736
You forced all of your husband's
key lieutenants out

00:06.770 --> 00:08.328
and replaced them
with women.

00:08.370 --> 00:10.736
I know how crazy
this is making you.

00:10.770 --> 00:14.501
Trying to convince everyone
I'm some sort of mastermind?

00:14.540 --> 00:16.349
You're under arrest.

00:16.380 --> 00:18.268
BELL: You have the right
to remain silent

00:18.310 --> 00:19.618
and refuse _to
answer questions.

00:19.650 --> 00:20.776
Hey, my dad called
this afternoon.

00:20.820 --> 00:23.482
He wants to take
us out to dinner.

00:23.520 --> 00:25.215
I'm sorry it's taken so long
for us to get together.

00:25.250 --> 00:26.285
You're remarkable.

00:27.590 --> 00:29.478
You know, you might have
to accept the fact

00:29.530 --> 00:31.225
that, whatever your relationship
with Andrew means,

00:31.260 --> 00:32.522
you just don't want it.

00:32.560 --> 00:34.699
Then what do I want?

00:34.730 --> 00:36.220
MAN:
Skim-milk late for Joan

00:36.270 --> 00:37.692
and whole-milk
latte for Andrew.

00:37.730 --> 00:39.288
Thank you.

00:39.340 --> 00:41.558
Oh. Excuse me.

00:41.600 --> 00:43.636
(clears throat)
Skim milk.

00:43.670 --> 00:45.501
I think you gave
me the wrong one.
Oh.

00:45.540 --> 00:47.576
Oh, my God.
What's wrong?
(gagging)

00:49.750 --> 00:52.639
Oh, my God.
Somebody call an ambulance!

00:52.680 --> 00:55.410
Andrew. Andrew.
(gagging, gasping)

01:00.860 --> 01:03.055
(door buzzes, opens)

01:05.560 --> 01:07.551
(door closes)

01:19.310 --> 01:21.403
Six days ago,

01:21.440 --> 01:23.249
my boyfriend Andrew Mittal
drank coffee

01:23.280 --> 01:25.669
from a cup with my name on it.

01:25.710 --> 01:27.746
It was laced
with hemlock.

01:27.780 --> 01:31.443
He died before
the ambulance got there.

01:31.490 --> 01:33.549
There was a woman
In the coffee shop

01:33.590 --> 01:35.387
wearing a blue leather jacket.

01:35.420 --> 01:40.153
She bumped into me when I was
picking up our drinks.

01:40.200 --> 01:41.895
Her name is Marion Desjardins.

01:41.930 --> 01:44.490
She's a French immigrant
living in the United States

01:44.530 --> 01:46.589
with a visa
from your old company.

01:46.640 --> 01:50.303
We bring in lots of people
from overseas.

01:50.340 --> 01:52.672
Consultants, mostly.

01:52.710 --> 01:55.406
Ms. Desjardins is an assassin.

01:55.440 --> 01:57.579
After we I.D.'d her,
we got a warrant

01:57.610 --> 02:00.579
to search her apartment
and found the hemlock plants.

02:00.620 --> 02:02.815
She confessed
to dosing my coffee,

02:02.850 --> 02:05.182
but claims it was
a random crime

02:05.220 --> 02:08.155
that had nothing
to do with you.

02:08.190 --> 02:10.351
So, how much are you
paying her for that?

02:10.390 --> 02:13.826
Even if you could get her
to admit that I paid her--

02:13.860 --> 02:17.364
which, by the way, I didn't--

02:17.400 --> 02:20.836
I'm already in this prison
until I die.

02:20.870 --> 02:22.906
Thanks to you.

02:22.940 --> 02:24.498
So...

02:24.540 --> 02:27.338
what are you doing here, Joan?

02:27.380 --> 02:30.304
Andrew was brilliant and kind.

02:30.350 --> 02:33.342
This rivalry
is between you and me.

02:33.380 --> 02:35.871
How can you be so naive?

02:35.920 --> 02:38.480
If he was involved
with you,

02:38.520 --> 02:41.216
he was involved with me.

02:42.260 --> 02:44.626
Take her away.

02:44.660 --> 02:47.754
You say this guy Andrew
was your boyfriend?

02:47.800 --> 02:50.519
The way I heard it, you were
breaking up with him that day.

02:52.270 --> 02:53.737
That must feel terrible.

02:53.770 --> 02:55.761
(door buzzes)

03:00.440 --> 03:02.476
GREGSON: We can't really
do anything with the fact

03:02.510 --> 03:03.943
that Elana March
said she knows

03:03.980 --> 03:05.777
what you and Andrew
were talking about,

03:05.810 --> 03:08.347
because there was a lot
of people In that coffee shop,

03:08.380 --> 03:09.984
and she could have heard that
from anyone.

03:10.020 --> 03:14.252
Now, that being said,
I know the warden over there,

03:14.290 --> 03:17.327
and he did a spot check
on her cell tonight.

03:17.360 --> 03:19.453
He found enough
contraband in there

03:19.500 --> 03:21.957
to put her in isolation
for a week or two.

03:22.000 --> 03:23.695
So she's not
gonna be talking

03:23.730 --> 03:26.267
to any of her friends
for a while.

03:26.300 --> 03:28.598
She's not gonna come
after me again.

03:28.640 --> 03:30.460
Not right away.

03:30.510 --> 03:31.966
She'll wait
till things die down.

03:32.010 --> 03:33.978
But just to be safe,

03:34.010 --> 03:36.308
you should switch up
your travel patterns,

03:36.350 --> 03:38.500
and I'm gonna put a unit
outside of your building.

03:40.750 --> 03:42.945
We'll keep you safe.

03:44.320 --> 03:45.947
Thanks.

03:53.800 --> 03:54.994
Uh, Watson,
I'll continue

03:55.030 --> 03:56.566
to bring food over
to your apartment

03:56.600 --> 03:58.329
if it's not too_much
of an Imposmon.

03:58.370 --> 04:00.736
You have a number of things
on your mind at the moment,

04:00.770 --> 04:03.034
and sustenance
needn't be one of them.

04:03.070 --> 04:05.561
As for our collaboration,
you just let me know

04:05.610 --> 04:07.305
when you're ready
to resume casework,

04:07.340 --> 04:08.830
and I won't intrude
until then.

04:08.880 --> 04:10.973
Thanks. It'll just be
a couple more days.

04:11.010 --> 04:12.045
Mm-hmm.

04:12.080 --> 04:15.379
Um, do you have counsel?

04:15.420 --> 04:16.978
It's been almost a week
since Andrew died.

04:17.020 --> 04:18.681
You've said almost
nothing about it.

04:18.720 --> 04:19.982
Which is your prerogative,
of course.

04:20.020 --> 04:21.578
Ijust... Iwant
to be certain

04:21.620 --> 04:24.418
that you have someone to, uh,
discuss the matter with.

04:24.460 --> 04:27.691
I'd offer my services
if you don't.

04:27.730 --> 04:28.992
(elevator bell clings)

04:29.030 --> 04:30.725
Andrew died because
he knew me.

04:30.770 --> 04:33.591
I don't really know what
else there is to say.

04:37.640 --> 04:40.871
MAN: Mr. Holmes, thank you
for agreeing to see me.

04:40.910 --> 04:44.471
We've actually met
before-- sort of.

04:44.510 --> 04:47.911
I moderate the discussion boards
at BeeCircuit.com.

04:49.750 --> 04:52.310
You're BeeBeeKing17.

04:52.360 --> 04:53.611
I am. (chuckles)

04:53.660 --> 04:54.809
You're a detective.

04:54.860 --> 04:56.009
I know from your posts.

04:56.060 --> 04:57.880
I have a bit
of a problem...

04:57.930 --> 04:59.750
I'm gonna stop you right there,
Mr. Joseph.

04:59.800 --> 05:00.892
I can't help you.

05:00.930 --> 05:02.795
You don't know what I'm asking.

05:02.830 --> 05:04.525
I don't need to.

05:04.570 --> 05:06.891
In the four years
I've frequented your Web site,

05:06.940 --> 05:09.090
I've sent you no fewer
than 13 letters

05:09.140 --> 05:11.631
detailing my proposed solutions
to the phenomenon

05:11.670 --> 05:13.501
known as colony
collapse disorder.

05:13.540 --> 05:16.646
You have sent me
exactly zero replies.

05:16.680 --> 05:18.898
You know how much
correspondence I get?

05:18.950 --> 05:20.076
I've got no idea.

05:20.120 --> 05:21.644
I do know, however,

05:21.680 --> 05:23.944
that mine is backed
by quality thinking.

05:23.990 --> 05:25.787
If you'd bothered
to find that out,

05:25.820 --> 05:27.515
you wouldn't find yourself
without a detective

05:27.560 --> 05:29.357
in your hour of need.

05:32.030 --> 05:34.851
Is there some way that I can
make this up to you?

05:34.900 --> 05:36.993
I suppose, if you were
to publish my theories

05:37.030 --> 05:39.737
on gamma rays
as a potential solution to CCD,

05:39.770 --> 05:41.658
then I might be able
to hear you out.

05:41.700 --> 05:43.406
Gamma rays?

05:43.440 --> 05:45.465
They... they've worked
in a couple instances,

05:45.510 --> 05:47.000
but they... they don't
scale as an answer.

05:47.040 --> 05:48.803
They're too dangerous.
You give John Q. Beekeeper

05:48.840 --> 05:50.740
access to gamma rays,
he'll melt his face off.

05:50.780 --> 05:53.476
A fact I addressed in
my most recent letter.

05:53.520 --> 05:54.669
Fine.

05:54.720 --> 05:57.143
Yeah, I'll put it
on the site.

05:57.190 --> 06:01.012
I also require that you change
your online user name.

06:01.060 --> 06:03.449
The cheap punnery
of "BeeBeeKing17"

06:03.490 --> 06:06.653
is offensive to musicians
and apIarlsts alike.

06:10.500 --> 06:13.094
You'll make the change?

06:14.140 --> 06:16.062
I guess.

06:16.100 --> 06:17.761
Good.

06:17.810 --> 06:20.438
So what seems to be the problem?

06:20.480 --> 06:23.847
How do you feel
about a field trip?

06:26.050 --> 06:28.712
MAN: I'm the assistant curator
of mammals here.

06:28.750 --> 06:30.786
HOLMES:
Your problem concerns zebras.

06:30.820 --> 06:34.711
More specifically,
the complete lack thereof.

06:34.760 --> 06:37.024
You've managed to lose track
of your zebras?

06:37.060 --> 06:39.756
Someone broke in here
and took them last night.

06:39.800 --> 06:41.995
Two females.
They're on loan to us

06:42.030 --> 06:44.169
because we're experts
in equine breeding.

06:44.200 --> 06:46.168
Breeding?

06:46.200 --> 06:49.636
Both the stolen animals
are pregnant.

06:49.670 --> 06:52.161
And they're due
in less than a week.

07:31.880 --> 07:34.542
Detective Bell, you're here.
Excellent.

07:34.580 --> 07:36.548
No, it's not
Detective Bell today.

07:36.590 --> 07:39.582
The department told me I had
too many vacation days built up,

07:39.620 --> 07:40.985
so I had to use them
or lose them.

07:41.020 --> 07:42.556
I'm aware
you're off duty.

07:42.590 --> 07:44.729
In fact, that's exactly
why I asked you here.

07:44.760 --> 07:46.227
I've picked up some
potentially interesting work

07:46.260 --> 07:47.591
involving stolen zebras.

07:47.630 --> 07:49.598
I thought it might be
an opportunity

07:49.630 --> 07:51.791
for you to gain
more exposure to my methods.

07:51.830 --> 07:54.663
You want me to work
a case With you?

07:54.700 --> 07:56.702
An informal setting is a more
fertile learning environment,

07:56.740 --> 07:57.832
don't you think?

07:57.870 --> 07:59.804
Think of it is a favor.

07:59.840 --> 08:02.001
So I'll work for you, and
somehow you're doing me a favor?

08:02.040 --> 08:03.871
Well, I do owe you a debt.
You'll recall

08:03.910 --> 08:05.571
the unfortunate business
with you and the bullet.

08:05.610 --> 08:07.271
I remember when
you got me shot.

08:07.320 --> 08:09.845
Look, I get it-- you want
somebody to talk at,

08:09.890 --> 08:12.108
but you don't want to
bother Joan right now?

08:12.150 --> 08:13.651
I will pay you.

08:13.690 --> 08:14.987
I'm already
getting paid today.

08:15.020 --> 08:16.885
A donation to the charity
of your choice, then.

08:16.930 --> 08:18.921
How'd you know I didn't
have plans for the day?

08:18.960 --> 08:21.155
People who are forced by
their employers to take time off

08:21.200 --> 08:23.998
don't generally have
thriving social lives.

08:24.030 --> 08:26.066
My rate to the
Harlem Youth Club.

08:26.100 --> 08:28.136
You keep track
of the hours.

08:29.170 --> 08:31.001
BELL: _
So you think

08:31.040 --> 08:32.735
someone just led
a couple zebras

08:32.780 --> 08:34.179
out the back door
and drove away?

08:36.610 --> 08:38.043
This loading dock
is the only

08:38.080 --> 08:39.616
relatively private
means of egress.

08:39.650 --> 08:41.777
I examined the _scene
before you arrived,

08:41.820 --> 08:43.947
and there were several fresh
hoofprints in the soil

08:43.990 --> 08:45.617
near one of the doors.

08:45.650 --> 08:47.754
Saw a few security cameras
in the zoo.

08:47.790 --> 08:49.781
Have you seen the footage?
There isn't any.

08:49.830 --> 08:51.582
Not coincidentally, the
power to the cameras

08:51.630 --> 08:53.723
was knocked out shortly
before the robbery.

08:53.760 --> 08:55.296
And that didn't trip
an alarm?

08:55.330 --> 08:57.798
This is a 200--
I don't think burglary

08:57.830 --> 08:59.969
is generally of
paramount concern.

09:00.000 --> 09:02.707
Now, there are two
sets of tire tracks

09:02.740 --> 09:04.105
within the loading dock.

09:04.140 --> 09:06.734
Tread is identical,
but one set of tracks

09:06.780 --> 09:09.169
is approximately one centimeter
deeper than the other.

09:09.210 --> 09:11.041
If you need me
to translate that

09:11.080 --> 09:12.616
into the idiom of_
American exceptionallsm,

09:12.650 --> 09:14.572
a centimeter is about
a third of an inch.

09:14.620 --> 09:15.917
I got it, thanks.

09:15.950 --> 09:18.111
So the first set of tracks
is when they drove up;

09:18.150 --> 09:20.050
the second one's deeper
because they had zebras

09:20.090 --> 09:22.183
in the back
when they drove away.

09:22.220 --> 09:24.927
Well deduced, Detective Bell.
I knew you'd make good company.

09:24.960 --> 09:27.622
Let me ask you something--
what do you think would happen

09:27.660 --> 09:30.060
if you call me by my first name?
You worried I'll take away

09:30.100 --> 09:31.067
your blood pudding or something?

09:31.100 --> 09:33.330
What? No.

09:33.370 --> 09:35.793
Good. 'Cause I don't even know
what blood pudding is.

09:35.840 --> 09:38.638
"Marcus" works just fine.

09:38.670 --> 09:40.206
Huh.

09:40.240 --> 09:42.947
Looks like they scraped
against the gate on the way out.

09:42.980 --> 09:46.143
So we're looking for a purple
truck with two pregnant zebras

09:46.180 --> 09:48.011
in the back.
These guys really know

09:48.050 --> 09:49.642
how to keep
a low profile.

09:49.690 --> 09:53.080
That might be better
camouflage than it seems.

09:53.120 --> 09:55.759
That shade of purple
is a proprietary color

09:55.790 --> 09:59.021
owned by Axiom Parcel
Delivery, or APD.

09:59.060 --> 10:00.925
It's almost impossible
to reproduce

10:00.960 --> 10:02.359
without the
company's consent.

10:02.400 --> 10:04.322
So, if you can't reproduce
the color,

10:04.370 --> 10:06.838
that means the thieves
stole an APD truck.

10:06.870 --> 10:08.337
Or they drive one.
Anyway, we should

10:08.370 --> 10:10.235
find out if
a truck's been stolen.

10:10.270 --> 10:12.329
Then what? I mean, these guys
aren't gonna be dumb enough

10:12.370 --> 10:14.372
to drive around with plates
that have been reported stolen.

10:14.410 --> 10:16.071
License plates
aren't the only way

10:16.110 --> 10:17.702
to find that truck,
Detective Bell.

10:17.750 --> 10:19.206
It's "Marcus."

10:23.020 --> 10:24.647
(door opens)

10:24.690 --> 10:26.817
BELL (calls):
Hello?
In here.

10:26.860 --> 10:27.918
(door closes)

10:29.860 --> 10:33.728
Why is your picture on the
wall at the Indian place?

10:33.760 --> 10:37.389
Oh. I helped the owner's family
resolve a misunderstanding

10:37.430 --> 10:40.194
having to do with caste system,
and they were very grateful.

10:40.240 --> 10:41.730
And now you're weighing
a toaster?

10:41.770 --> 10:43.237
Finally got through

10:43.270 --> 10:44.828
to Axiom Parcel Delivery's
corporate office.

10:44.870 --> 10:46.735
It seems
one of their trucks was stolen

10:46.780 --> 10:48.236
eight days ago in Queens.

10:48.280 --> 10:50.202
Apparently, the driver left
one of the vehicles running

10:50.250 --> 10:52.002
when he went _inside
on a home delivery,

10:52.050 --> 10:55.247
and when he emerged, the truck
and its cargo were gone.

10:55.280 --> 10:58.818
Very likely, that's the truck
used in the zoo robbery.

10:58.850 --> 11:02.729
You say that like it explains
why you're weighing a toaster.

11:02.760 --> 11:04.227
APD were kind enough

11:04.260 --> 11:06.421
to send over the truck's
manifest for that day.

11:06.460 --> 11:08.325
I have listed it here.

11:08.360 --> 11:11.090
For each package,
we know the sender's address,

11:11.130 --> 11:13.963
the recipient's address
and the weight of each parcel.

11:14.000 --> 11:16.366
Using that information,
I'm attempting to identify

11:16.400 --> 11:19.233
the contents of each box.

11:19.270 --> 11:21.477
I'm weighing the probable
objects that I have handy,

11:21.510 --> 11:24.240
and relying on weights listed
online for ones that I do not.

11:24.280 --> 11:25.838
How is this supposed
to help us?

11:27.080 --> 11:29.173
It already has.
Package number 27.

11:29.220 --> 11:34.214
From Pet Junction in Chicago
to Seth Buxton, Bayside--

11:34.260 --> 11:36.251
12 pounds, nine ounces.

11:36.290 --> 11:38.224
The weight of the package
is the sum of the weights

11:38.260 --> 11:40.854
of a water bowl, a package of
canine treats and a tail trail.

11:40.900 --> 11:42.322
What's a tail trail?

11:42.360 --> 11:43.827
It's a pet collar

11:43.870 --> 11:45.326
which features
a GPS tracking chip.

11:45.370 --> 11:47.133
The collar
comes precharged,

11:47.170 --> 11:49.092
which means the tracking chip
is already active,

11:49.140 --> 11:51.461
even before it's opened, so if
we can find the tracking chip,

11:51.510 --> 11:53.330
we might be able
to find the stolen truck.

11:53.380 --> 11:57.202
Or it'll take us to some guy
who bought stolen pet supplies.

11:57.250 --> 12:01.346
Either way, it's a leap
we did not have one hour ago.

12:01.380 --> 12:03.280
How much chili powder's in here?

12:03.320 --> 12:04.810
The restaurant has instructions

12:04.850 --> 12:06.909
to make my orders
as picante as they can.

12:06.960 --> 12:08.416
Did you tell them
you were ordering for two?

12:08.460 --> 12:10.325
No.

12:10.360 --> 12:11.850
I'll go tech assist.

12:11.890 --> 12:14.199
They should have GPS
on the collar soon.

12:14.230 --> 12:17.393
Then I guess
I'll order another lunch.

12:17.430 --> 12:19.933
BELL:
Looks like the guy who stole

12:19.970 --> 12:22.234
the truck just
dumped the boxes here.

12:26.170 --> 12:28.434
So, uh...

12:28.480 --> 12:30.903
how's Joan doing aanay?

12:30.950 --> 12:32.815
I haven't seen her
since the funeral.

12:32.850 --> 12:34.147
I don't know.

12:34.180 --> 12:35.977
All I know is,
she's not doing well,

12:36.020 --> 12:37.942
but other than that,
she's not confided in me.

12:37.990 --> 12:39.287
So when you two aren't

12:39.320 --> 12:41.379
working a case, what happens?

12:41.420 --> 12:43.786
You just sit around
in contemplative silence?

12:43.830 --> 12:45.525
I'm not opposed
to a productive silence,

12:45.560 --> 12:47.926
but in this case,
I have offered to listen.

12:47.960 --> 12:51.259
My first partner was involved
in a shooting

12:51.300 --> 12:53.791
eight weeks into the job.

12:53.840 --> 12:57.105
I let him walk around with PTSD
for the next six months.

12:57.140 --> 12:59.108
I offered to help, too,

12:59.140 --> 13:01.938
but we didn't get anywhere
until I insisted.

13:04.910 --> 13:06.172
You find something?

13:06.210 --> 13:07.518
I don't know.

13:07.550 --> 13:09.142
It's a receipt.

13:09.180 --> 13:10.989
Or at least, it was.

13:11.020 --> 13:12.510
(sniffles)

13:12.550 --> 13:14.415
(panﬁng)

13:14.460 --> 13:18.282
Modern receipts are printed
often with thermal ink.

13:18.330 --> 13:20.525
It helps the text
appear sharp and clean.

13:20.560 --> 13:22.289
Trouble is, it fades

13:22.330 --> 13:23.592
rather quickly.

13:23.630 --> 13:25.166
Unless you heat it.

13:25.200 --> 13:26.929
Precisely.

13:29.940 --> 13:32.568
"855 North Sullivan
Street, Brooklyn."

13:32.610 --> 13:34.999
It is, apparently, the
address of "Criterion

13:35.040 --> 13:37.201
Equine Veterinary Services."

13:37.250 --> 13:38.478
A horse hospital.

13:38.510 --> 13:41.149
This may not be here
by coincidence.

13:41.180 --> 13:42.442
Someone here might
have something

13:42.480 --> 13:45.483
to do with our
stolen zebras.

13:48.360 --> 13:51.022
