30:26.950 --> 30:28.315
Been shopping.

30:28.360 --> 30:30.055
Yeah, you've been great
the past few days,

30:30.090 --> 30:31.626
but, you know, it's time
to get off the couch.

30:31.660 --> 30:34.094
Well, you'll be pleased
to know that your nudge

30:34.130 --> 30:36.451
towards Letchworth Village
paid off.

30:36.500 --> 30:38.593
This afternoon,
Detective Bell and I identified

30:38.630 --> 30:40.598
the zebra-stealing murderer
as a zoo employee

30:40.630 --> 30:41.858
named Ben Reynolds.

30:41.900 --> 30:43.197
He refused to give us

30:43.240 --> 30:45.458
a DNA sample,
so I placed a call to my contact

30:45.510 --> 30:47.364
at the zoo, who happily
dug through the trash

30:47.410 --> 30:49.275
and found a can
of the grape soda

30:49.310 --> 30:51.346
preferred by Mr. Reynolds.

30:51.380 --> 30:54.076
And preliminary DNA test results
indicate a match.

30:54.120 --> 30:55.644
Bell and his merry men

30:55.680 --> 30:58.148
are on their way
to make an arrest as we speak.

30:59.150 --> 31:00.378
What is it?

31:00.420 --> 31:02.251
Look at the return zip code.

31:02.290 --> 31:04.155
It's the same place as
the prison they're keeping

31:04.190 --> 31:06.226
Elana March.
I doubt that's her handwriting.

31:06.260 --> 31:09.195
She'd have found someone
to send it on her behalf.

31:09.230 --> 31:11.994
We can call captain and tell him
there's been a threat.

31:12.030 --> 31:14.134
(phone ringing)

31:14.170 --> 31:16.934
Detective Bell.
Mr. Reynolds in custody?

31:16.970 --> 31:18.562
BELL:
Ben Reynolds is in the wind.

31:18.610 --> 31:20.498
Well, how's that possible?
You had men watching him.

31:20.540 --> 31:22.531
You should get over here.

31:24.010 --> 31:26.274
Go. I'll call Gregson.
This is just

31:26.310 --> 31:27.971
Elana trying to get
inside my head.

31:34.520 --> 31:36.010
Reynolds came home at 4:30.

31:36.060 --> 31:38.221
We had a unit on the
front and back door.

31:38.260 --> 31:41.297
He never left. Now, we show
up to arrest him at 6:30,

31:41.330 --> 31:44.959
and the place is empty.

31:45.000 --> 31:47.218
I take it you've searched
the other apartments

31:47.270 --> 31:49.431
in the building?
He's nowhere.

31:49.470 --> 31:52.564
It's like the guy
vanished into thin air.

32:12.260 --> 32:13.227
You know the slang

32:13.260 --> 32:15.421
"to eighty-six," meaning
to get rid of something,

32:15.460 --> 32:18.725
originated in a New York
speakeasy called Chumley's?

32:18.770 --> 32:20.169
No.

32:20.200 --> 32:22.088
You see,
the rear entrance of the bar

32:25.270 --> 32:28.501
Now, when the manager got word
that a raid was on its way,

32:28.540 --> 32:30.303
he would eighty-six his patrons.

32:30.340 --> 32:32.103
He would rush them
out of the back door,

32:32.150 --> 32:33.503
the 86 Bedford Street door,

32:33.550 --> 32:36.439
while he greeted police
at the front.

32:36.480 --> 32:38.641
I assume you're going somewhere
with this.

32:38.690 --> 32:41.488
Well, as it happens,
we're standing across the street

32:41.520 --> 32:45.320
from the building
that used to house Chumley's.

32:45.360 --> 32:49.251
Now, police of the era
could never determine exactly...

32:49.300 --> 32:50.995
how Chumley's

32:51.030 --> 32:54.431
was bringing bootleg liquor
into the building.

32:55.640 --> 32:58.507
Turns out, there was
a network of tunnels

32:58.540 --> 33:02.408
leading from the speakeasy
to the adjacent buildings...

33:02.440 --> 33:04.044
(floor creaking)

33:04.080 --> 33:06.173
...buildings the police
weren't watching.

33:08.050 --> 33:11.087
Care to have a guess what's
underneath these floorboards?

33:13.790 --> 33:15.985
(hinges creak)

33:20.590 --> 33:24.321
Ben Reynolds didn't
vanish into thin air.

33:24.370 --> 33:27.191
_He vanished
Into a tunnel.

33:33.470 --> 33:36.598
Ben Reynolds is wanted
for the murder of David Chang.

33:36.640 --> 33:40.440
The case against him is strong,
so he has no choice but to flee.

33:40.480 --> 33:42.448
He's an indebted
graduate student

33:42.480 --> 33:44.710
with very few
material assets.

33:44.750 --> 33:47.082
If he wants to finance
his life on the run,

33:47.120 --> 33:50.578
he has precisely one chip
which he can and must cash in:

33:50.620 --> 33:53.327
an infant quagga.

33:53.360 --> 33:55.225
These are the facts.

33:55.260 --> 33:57.057
Questions?

33:57.100 --> 33:58.362
Yes.

33:58.400 --> 33:59.719
What am I doing here?

33:59.770 --> 34:02.591
I mean, we had a
work day. It ended.

34:02.640 --> 34:06.098
The normal thing is to go our
separate ways for a few hours.

34:08.110 --> 34:09.577
The fire of deduction
cannot be kindled

34:09.610 --> 34:12.147
without the frisson
of person-to-person contact.

34:12.180 --> 34:13.499
If you want
to work together,

34:13.550 --> 34:15.347
you need to get used
to working odd hours.

34:15.380 --> 34:17.678
Hey. I've been working this case
as a cop

34:17.720 --> 34:19.381
ever since
we found Chang's corpse.

34:19.420 --> 34:20.409
Regardless.

34:20.450 --> 34:22.213
The lines are blurred.

34:22.260 --> 34:24.148
You are committed to seeing
this through via my methods.

34:25.660 --> 34:27.628
We have no idea

34:27.660 --> 34:29.218
where Reynolds is;
a search of his apartment

34:29.260 --> 34:31.569
has yielded no clues
as to where he is keeping

34:31.600 --> 34:34.091
his one remaining quagga.

34:34.140 --> 34:36.461
He does, however,
have to sell the beast.

34:36.500 --> 34:38.468
Our best chance
of a quick apprehension

34:38.510 --> 34:40.535
is to pose as buyers
and then arrest him

34:40.570 --> 34:41.537
at the point of transaction.

34:41.580 --> 34:43.104
How do we do that?

34:43.140 --> 34:44.607
This guy knows
we're looking for him.

34:44.650 --> 34:46.345
He's not gonna put out
a want ad.

34:46.380 --> 34:48.678
No, but he will want to create
a vigorous marketplace

34:48.720 --> 34:50.347
for the animal.

34:50.380 --> 34:52.211
There is, at this moment,

34:52.250 --> 34:54.218
a bidding war
happening somewhere.

34:54.260 --> 34:57.752
All we need to do is find it
and win it.

34:57.790 --> 34:59.382
What's this?

34:59.430 --> 35:01.250
This is everything I could find
on criminal cases

35:01.300 --> 35:03.495
involving the sale
of endangered animals.

35:03.530 --> 35:06.124
There's a global marketplace
for these unfortunate creatures.

35:06.170 --> 35:08.138
It's clandestine,
but there must be a way

35:08.170 --> 35:09.831
to connect the buyers
with the sellers.

35:09.870 --> 35:12.703
So you think there's, what, some
kind of code these guys use?

35:12.740 --> 35:14.708
You know, there are people
who work this stuff full-time.

35:14.740 --> 35:16.378
Don't you think
they would have found it by now?

35:16.410 --> 35:19.573
People, Detective Bell,
are not you and me.

35:26.420 --> 35:28.479
(alarm clock ringing)

35:33.190 --> 35:35.192
(ringing stops)

35:43.340 --> 35:46.559
You want to tell me why we're
having breakfast in Greenpoint?

35:46.610 --> 35:48.669
You made it.
Excellent.

35:48.710 --> 35:51.577
Took the liberty
of ordering for you.

35:51.610 --> 35:54.340
Ah. I don't eat red meat.

35:54.380 --> 35:56.416
A man of hidden depths.

35:56.450 --> 35:58.418
We're here
because this cafe

35:58.450 --> 36:01.351
affords us the
best vantage pomt.

36:01.390 --> 36:03.585
Shortly after you fell
asleep last night,

36:03.620 --> 36:05.520
I realized there
was a common factor

36:05.560 --> 36:07.858
_ in several recent
Illegal anImal trades.

36:07.890 --> 36:11.860
In each case, the transaction
was arranged via a classified ad

36:11.900 --> 36:14.562
placed on a Web site that
deals in animal trading.

36:14.600 --> 36:17.694
Most of the buying and selling
on there, perfectly legitimate,

36:17.740 --> 36:20.368
but every once in
a while, there's an ad

36:20.410 --> 36:23.379
which features the phrase
"once in a blue moon."

36:23.410 --> 36:25.503
Is that one
of our unmarked vans?

36:25.550 --> 36:30.374
"Once in a blue moon" functions
as a dog thstle In those ads.

36:30.420 --> 36:33.241
It's used to signal that
endangered or outlawed animals

36:33.290 --> 36:34.780
are for sale.

36:34.820 --> 36:37.516
And you found an ad last night
using that phrase?

36:37.560 --> 36:39.448
Five, actually.

36:39.490 --> 36:41.924
It seems that Ben
Reynolds Is rather keen

36:41.960 --> 36:44.269
to peddle his
equine wares.

36:44.300 --> 36:47.519
I contacted him, pretending
to be a man named Sigerson.

36:47.570 --> 36:49.265
Why Sigerson?

36:49.300 --> 36:51.860
It's a pseudonym
I use occasionally.

36:51.910 --> 36:54.538
Mmm. I outbid
the others,

36:54.580 --> 36:56.878
arranged a meeting,
contacted Captain Gregson.

36:56.910 --> 36:59.276
Here we are.

36:59.310 --> 37:01.005
The two parties are
meant to inspect things

37:01.050 --> 37:04.645
to their mutual satisfaction
and then switch cars.

37:04.690 --> 37:06.942
That's Reynolds.

37:08.290 --> 37:09.917
Why aren't
they arresting him?

37:09.960 --> 37:11.825
They haven't seen
the quagga yet.

37:20.030 --> 37:21.668
(sirens wailing)

37:21.700 --> 37:23.258
(tires screeching)

37:23.300 --> 37:25.302
OFFICER:
Freeze!

37:27.710 --> 37:30.929
You know, I could have arranged
all this with the department.

37:30.980 --> 37:32.675
You were asleep.

37:48.730 --> 37:51.051
It was a pleasure, Holmes.

37:51.100 --> 37:54.934
No, the pleasure was mine
and mine alone, Marcus.

